node.text:
Don't bug out! Cicada season is approaching in many states, so @marascampo and I did a quick Q&A with entomologist, Mike Deutsch ⬇️ 

➡️ How often do cicadas appear? 

➡️ How long are cicadas around for?

➡️ Are cicadas dangerous? 

➡️ Why do cicadas make so much noise!?

➡️ Is there anything I can do to repel cicadas? 

For more on this topic, plus travel + safety tips from @thepointsguy, be sure to watch #TheDrOzShow tomorrow. 
.
.
.
#Summer #Bugs #Cicadas #CicadaSeason #BugsLife

While the CDC and FDA have recommended the U.S. pause using the J&J vaccine out of "an abundance of caution," Dr. Peter Hotez has a message for those who've already gotten the shot: "Don’t panic. Don’t worry." 
.
.
.
#COVID19 #Health #COVIDvaccine #COVIDupdate

node.text:
Breaking News: President Biden just announced all adults will be eligible on April 19 for the vaccine—nearly two weeks ahead of schedule. We talked to the @u.s.surgeongeneral about this, and his hopes for the #wecandothis campaign to end vaccine hesitancy.

We’ll have more with Dr. Murthy tomorrow on #TheDrOzShow. Be sure to tune in.

node.text:
Almost 6 years ago, Alex Trebek surprised me on #TheDrOzShow for our 1,000th episode. He really got me good, and his memory will forever bring me joy. 

It's truly been an honor to guest host Jeopardy! these past two weeks. I'm looking forward to our last episode today. I hope you'll tune in.

node.text:
If you're looking for a delicious and beautiful Easter breakfast or brunch dish, this hash brown quiche has it all. Packed with asparagus, goat cheese, shallots and chives, this quiche will deliver with every bite. 

Let me know if you plan on adding this to your Easter menu in the comments. ⬇️ 

Grab the recipe on my Story or on doctoroz.com

node.title: Easter Hash Brown Quiche With Asparagus & Goat Cheese

node.text: Happy birthday, @lisaoz. You’ve brought joy to my life on every single day of our 36 year marriage. You continue to be a beacon of light, continually remind me that people need love before knowledge, and always ask the extra question, which is an especially powerful tool when raising four kids. I hope other couples feel the same passion we do. I love you.
